WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.140 align:middle line:90%


00:00:06.140 --> 00:00:08.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Is there a deeper, more
hidden esoteric meaning

00:00:08.720 --> 00:00:10.820 align:middle line:84%
to the Hollywood films
that we all love to watch?

00:00:10.820 --> 00:00:11.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm Jay Dyer.

00:00:11.730 --> 00:00:12.740 align:middle line:90%
>> And I'm Jay Weidner.

00:00:12.740 --> 00:00:14.310 align:middle line:90%
This is Hollywood Decoded.

00:00:14.310 --> 00:00:17.286 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:17.286 --> 00:00:25.230 align:middle line:90%


00:00:25.230 --> 00:00:27.660 align:middle line:84%
>> The "Terminator" series is
one of the most fascinating

00:00:27.660 --> 00:00:29.550 align:middle line:84%
examples of predictive
programming,

00:00:29.550 --> 00:00:31.950 align:middle line:84%
especially when we think about
the fact that it premiered

00:00:31.950 --> 00:00:33.240 align:middle line:90%
in the '80s.

00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:36.000 align:middle line:10%
And what's neat about that is
that most people in the '80s

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:39.724 align:middle line:10%
had not really had this idea of
an internet or what was coming.

00:00:39.724 --> 00:00:41.640 align:middle line:84%
Maybe if you worked in
government or something

00:00:41.640 --> 00:00:43.740 align:middle line:84%
like that at some
sort of secret base,

00:00:43.740 --> 00:00:48.090 align:middle line:84%
you knew about the experiments
and-- and data transmissions

00:00:48.090 --> 00:00:49.556 align:middle line:90%
that ARPANET had done.

00:00:49.556 --> 00:00:51.930 align:middle line:84%
But you didn't know about this
coming internet that would

00:00:51.930 --> 00:00:53.880 align:middle line:90%
really change the entire world.

00:00:53.880 --> 00:00:56.310 align:middle line:84%
However, there were a lot
of films, and in particular,

00:00:56.310 --> 00:00:58.350 align:middle line:84%
the "Terminator" series,
which encapsulated

00:00:58.350 --> 00:01:02.490 align:middle line:84%
this prediction of a coming
not just interlinked computer

00:01:02.490 --> 00:01:04.730 align:middle line:84%
network, but the
actual idea of AI

00:01:04.730 --> 00:01:09.300 align:middle line:84%
in a giant space-based
Skynet network.

00:01:09.300 --> 00:01:12.810 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we had in
the "Terminator" series.

00:01:12.810 --> 00:01:15.370 align:middle line:84%
>> Skynet is the bad guy,
I guess you could say,

00:01:15.370 --> 00:01:16.470 align:middle line:90%
in the series.

00:01:16.470 --> 00:01:20.700 align:middle line:84%
And it directs the terminators
to go do its will on Earth,

00:01:20.700 --> 00:01:23.910 align:middle line:84%
to kill the rebels
and things like that.

00:01:23.910 --> 00:01:28.080 align:middle line:84%
The whole idea, though,
that a guy from Canada

00:01:28.080 --> 00:01:33.270 align:middle line:84%
can come down to the United
States and be a truck driver

00:01:33.270 --> 00:01:35.970 align:middle line:84%
and work at a drugstore
like James Cameron

00:01:35.970 --> 00:01:39.810 align:middle line:84%
did and then one day come up
with this idea for a script.

00:01:39.810 --> 00:01:41.850 align:middle line:84%
And then he, you
know, then he insists

00:01:41.850 --> 00:01:44.640 align:middle line:84%
that he directs it even though
he has really no filmmaking

00:01:44.640 --> 00:01:46.370 align:middle line:90%
background at all.

00:01:46.370 --> 00:01:48.900 align:middle line:84%
And the fact that
then, you know,

00:01:48.900 --> 00:01:50.460 align:middle line:90%
he does a pretty good job.

00:01:50.460 --> 00:01:54.060 align:middle line:90%
And then, it becomes a huge hit.

00:01:54.060 --> 00:01:56.760 align:middle line:10%
The whole thing just
seems dubious to me.

00:01:56.760 --> 00:01:59.532 align:middle line:84%
As far as my own
experiences in Hollywood,

00:01:59.532 --> 00:02:00.990 align:middle line:84%
you really have to
work your way up

00:02:00.990 --> 00:02:02.340 align:middle line:90%
or you have to know somebody.

00:02:02.340 --> 00:02:03.650 align:middle line:90%
And clearly he did neither.

00:02:03.650 --> 00:02:05.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he did work for
Roger Corman for a while,

00:02:05.940 --> 00:02:09.900 align:middle line:84%
but not really long enough
to gain a lot of contacts.

00:02:09.900 --> 00:02:13.320 align:middle line:84%
And so I don't know what
his background really is.

00:02:13.320 --> 00:02:15.000 align:middle line:84%
I--I suspect that
there's more to it.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:16.560 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:02:16.560 --> 00:02:18.580 align:middle line:84%
He comes from the
Camerons of Canada,

00:02:18.580 --> 00:02:21.210 align:middle line:84%
which are a very prominent
family in Canada.

00:02:21.210 --> 00:02:24.450 align:middle line:84%
We have Ewan Cameron running
the mind control experiments out

00:02:24.450 --> 00:02:25.680 align:middle line:90%
of Montreal.

00:02:25.680 --> 00:02:29.100 align:middle line:84%
We have Marjorie Cameron, who
is the wife of Jack Parsons.

00:02:29.100 --> 00:02:31.020 align:middle line:90%
She is also from Canada.

00:02:31.020 --> 00:02:34.410 align:middle line:84%
And it just-- the whole
thing seemed dubious.

00:02:34.410 --> 00:02:37.000 align:middle line:84%
And I wonder if he doesn't
have a background connected

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:37.800 align:middle line:90%
to DARPA.

00:02:37.800 --> 00:02:41.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he is a smart guy, and
he wouldn't make a big show out

00:02:41.940 --> 00:02:42.820 align:middle line:90%
of it.

00:02:42.820 --> 00:02:45.540 align:middle line:84%
But the fact that there are
other Camerons associated

00:02:45.540 --> 00:02:48.510 align:middle line:84%
with intel and things
like that makes

00:02:48.510 --> 00:02:50.640 align:middle line:84%
me wonder if there
isn't something more

00:02:50.640 --> 00:02:51.720 align:middle line:90%
to James Cameron.

00:02:51.720 --> 00:02:52.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:02:52.570 --> 00:02:53.370 align:middle line:90%
>> But.

00:02:53.370 --> 00:02:55.590 align:middle line:10%
The great thing is
is that he starts out

00:02:55.590 --> 00:03:00.000 align:middle line:10%
the series with a flash-bang
B-movie action film.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.350 align:middle line:10%
And then he-- he in the next
film starts getting in to what

00:03:04.350 --> 00:03:06.960 align:middle line:10%
the implications of this AI--

00:03:06.960 --> 00:03:09.360 align:middle line:10%
and it is for all of humanity.

00:03:09.360 --> 00:03:11.830 align:middle line:84%
And then the rest of the
series really drills down deep

00:03:11.830 --> 00:03:12.630 align:middle line:90%
into that.

00:03:12.630 --> 00:03:13.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:03:13.380 --> 00:03:15.150 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that's kind of what
we want to explore in this

00:03:15.150 --> 00:03:15.430 align:middle line:90%
show.

00:03:15.430 --> 00:03:15.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:03:15.710 --> 00:03:17.460 align:middle line:10%
I see something very
analogous to what we

00:03:17.460 --> 00:03:18.900 align:middle line:10%
discussed with Philip K. Dick.

00:03:18.900 --> 00:03:20.520 align:middle line:10%
I think that James
Cameron had to have

00:03:20.520 --> 00:03:23.400 align:middle line:10%
had some kind of connection,
some kind of inside link

00:03:23.400 --> 00:03:26.760 align:middle line:10%
to what Silicon Valley, what
Stanford Research Institute was

00:03:26.760 --> 00:03:29.220 align:middle line:10%
up to in the process of
creating the internet.

00:03:29.220 --> 00:03:31.130 align:middle line:84%
Because the internet
comes out of the '60s.

00:03:31.130 --> 00:03:34.200 align:middle line:84%
You know, but by the '80s,
it's obviously being more--

00:03:34.200 --> 00:03:35.460 align:middle line:90%
it's a lot more advanced.

00:03:35.460 --> 00:03:38.297 align:middle line:84%
And you have in the late
'70s Reagan and Star Wars

00:03:38.297 --> 00:03:40.880 align:middle line:84%
Defense Initiative saying that
we're going to weaponize space.

00:03:40.880 --> 00:03:44.130 align:middle line:84%
And that's the whole principle
behind this whole-- this move,

00:03:44.130 --> 00:03:46.470 align:middle line:84%
that-- that--
everything that changes

00:03:46.470 --> 00:03:48.600 align:middle line:84%
from the '70s into
the '80s based

00:03:48.600 --> 00:03:50.100 align:middle line:90%
around space-based weapons.

00:03:50.100 --> 00:03:53.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, a lot of stuff was
happening in the early '80s.

00:03:53.790 --> 00:03:55.550 align:middle line:90%
We have-- we know from--

00:03:55.550 --> 00:03:58.360 align:middle line:84%
from our insiders that the
Secret Space Program really

00:03:58.360 --> 00:03:59.160 align:middle line:90%
took off.

00:03:59.160 --> 00:04:01.800 align:middle line:84%
And they developed these
really new technologies

00:04:01.800 --> 00:04:04.680 align:middle line:84%
that Reagan talks about in
his diary about ships that

00:04:04.680 --> 00:04:06.877 align:middle line:90%
can take 300 people into space.

00:04:06.877 --> 00:04:09.210 align:middle line:84%
And everyone thought he was
a whack job when he said it,

00:04:09.210 --> 00:04:10.620 align:middle line:90%
but actually, he wasn't.

00:04:10.620 --> 00:04:14.130 align:middle line:84%
And also, CIA is really
basically infiltrating

00:04:14.130 --> 00:04:15.690 align:middle line:90%
Hollywood at this point.

00:04:15.690 --> 00:04:17.691 align:middle line:84%
And that's another
point about Cameron.

00:04:17.691 --> 00:04:19.440 align:middle line:84%
You've got to wonder
what's going on here.

00:04:19.440 --> 00:04:21.779 align:middle line:84%
And it's almost like
the "Terminator"--

00:04:21.779 --> 00:04:25.230 align:middle line:84%
the first two-- were the
deepest, darkest fears

00:04:25.230 --> 00:04:27.830 align:middle line:84%
of the people that were
working inside DARPA.

00:04:27.830 --> 00:04:29.940 align:middle line:84%
They've taken,
extrapolated their ideas

00:04:29.940 --> 00:04:31.590 align:middle line:84%
all the way to the
end, and they were

00:04:31.590 --> 00:04:33.190 align:middle line:90%
realizing where this was going.

00:04:33.190 --> 00:04:33.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Exactly

00:04:33.990 --> 00:04:36.515 align:middle line:84%
>> Because early as the early
'80s, I think that-- that--

00:04:36.515 --> 00:04:39.120 align:middle line:84%
they-- you know, they Cameron,
this is not a good thing that

00:04:39.120 --> 00:04:40.270 align:middle line:90%
we're building here.

00:04:40.270 --> 00:04:41.520 align:middle line:90%
And we need to warn the world.

00:04:41.520 --> 00:04:41.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:04:41.940 --> 00:04:43.480 align:middle line:84%
>> That's what I
think is going on.

00:04:43.480 --> 00:04:45.630 align:middle line:84%
>> So here, we're going
to move to "Terminator 2,"

00:04:45.630 --> 00:04:47.880 align:middle line:84%
because "Terminator" one
basically just sets the stage

00:04:47.880 --> 00:04:48.680 align:middle line:90%
for the storyline.

00:04:48.680 --> 00:04:51.510 align:middle line:84%
And then we--we get into
the real heavy stuff in 2

00:04:51.510 --> 00:04:53.100 align:middle line:90%
and in the rest of the sequels.

00:04:53.100 --> 00:04:55.170 align:middle line:84%
And what we have here
is Skynet basically

00:04:55.170 --> 00:04:57.000 align:middle line:90%
sets a date for the apocalypse.

00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:59.640 align:middle line:84%
And the way I read a lot of
this is that it's going to be,

00:04:59.640 --> 00:05:01.530 align:middle line:84%
essentially, a kind of
psychological warfare.

00:05:01.530 --> 00:05:04.080 align:middle line:84%
I don't really think that we're
about to see the apocalypse.

00:05:04.080 --> 00:05:06.600 align:middle line:84%
But I think that the Pentagon,
military-industrial complex

00:05:06.600 --> 00:05:10.350 align:middle line:84%
likes to play with the idea
that the apocalypse could

00:05:10.350 --> 00:05:13.266 align:middle line:84%
be at any moment and the
fear that that causes.

00:05:13.266 --> 00:05:14.640 align:middle line:84%
And this whole
idea is really out

00:05:14.640 --> 00:05:17.240 align:middle line:84%
of the Cold War and
mutually-assured destruction

00:05:17.240 --> 00:05:19.860 align:middle line:84%
and that the Soviets are going
to nuke us at any moment.

00:05:19.860 --> 00:05:21.720 align:middle line:90%
And get under your desk, right?

00:05:21.720 --> 00:05:24.585 align:middle line:84%
Which makes no sense, because if
a nuke blast is coming, right,

00:05:24.585 --> 00:05:26.020 align:middle line:84%
like what is the
desk going to do?

00:05:26.020 --> 00:05:27.400 align:middle line:84%
So then, you're just going
to melt under the desk

00:05:27.400 --> 00:05:29.440 align:middle line:84%
instead of on top of
the desk or something.

00:05:29.440 --> 00:05:32.050 align:middle line:90%
So I think that it's--

00:05:32.050 --> 00:05:34.780 align:middle line:84%
on one level, it's kind
of psychological warfare

00:05:34.780 --> 00:05:35.650 align:middle line:90%
for the public.

00:05:35.650 --> 00:05:37.630 align:middle line:84%
But I also think that
it's telling us more

00:05:37.630 --> 00:05:40.151 align:middle line:90%
about philosophical questions.

00:05:40.151 --> 00:05:41.650 align:middle line:84%
The series is going
to ask questions

00:05:41.650 --> 00:05:46.329 align:middle line:84%
about predestination,
predetermined futures,

00:05:46.329 --> 00:05:47.620 align:middle line:90%
and whether there is free will.

00:05:47.620 --> 00:05:49.540 align:middle line:84%
And of course, bots
don't have free will.

00:05:49.540 --> 00:05:51.190 align:middle line:84%
That's going to
be in the dialogue

00:05:51.190 --> 00:05:54.730 align:middle line:84%
with John Connor and
Arnold, the Terminator.

00:05:54.730 --> 00:05:56.260 align:middle line:90%
>> And time loops also.

00:05:56.260 --> 00:05:57.060 align:middle line:90%
>> And time loops.

00:05:57.060 --> 00:05:58.809 align:middle line:84%
>> How you get-- get
caught in time loops.

00:05:58.809 --> 00:06:00.220 align:middle line:90%
And the future becomes the past.

00:06:00.220 --> 00:06:01.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Which was big in the '80s.

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:03.457 align:middle line:84%
The '80s were obsessed with
time loops or something.

00:06:03.457 --> 00:06:05.290 align:middle line:84%
What we're looking at
here is Skynet setting

00:06:05.290 --> 00:06:08.210 align:middle line:90%
the date for the attacks, 1984.

00:06:08.210 --> 00:06:11.550 align:middle line:10%
>> The computer which
controlled the machines, Skynet,

00:06:11.550 --> 00:06:15.170 align:middle line:10%
sent two terminators
back through time.

00:06:15.170 --> 00:06:16.280 align:middle line:10%
Their mission?

00:06:16.280 --> 00:06:19.370 align:middle line:10%
To destroy the leader
of the human resistance,

00:06:19.370 --> 00:06:22.118 align:middle line:10%
John Connor, my son.

00:06:22.118 --> 00:06:23.570 align:middle line:10%
[EXPLOSIONS]

00:06:23.570 --> 00:06:25.990 align:middle line:10%


00:06:25.990 --> 00:06:27.670 align:middle line:10%
The first terminator
was programmed

00:06:27.670 --> 00:06:32.890 align:middle line:10%
to strike at me in the year
1984, before John was born.

00:06:32.890 --> 00:06:34.890 align:middle line:10%
It failed.

00:06:34.890 --> 00:06:37.730 align:middle line:10%
The second was set to
strike at John himself

00:06:37.730 --> 00:06:38.840 align:middle line:10%
when he was still a child.

00:06:38.840 --> 00:06:42.129 align:middle line:90%


00:06:42.129 --> 00:06:44.170 align:middle line:84%
>> So here we have a kind
of playing with, again,

00:06:44.170 --> 00:06:45.250 align:middle line:90%
the Christ mythos.

00:06:45.250 --> 00:06:46.970 align:middle line:84%
If you remember from
part one, there's

00:06:46.970 --> 00:06:50.650 align:middle line:84%
a semi-miraculous birth for
this character of John Connor.

00:06:50.650 --> 00:06:54.820 align:middle line:84%
And he's going to be the,
sort of, human savior.

00:06:54.820 --> 00:06:59.200 align:middle line:84%
But the salvation is not from
some sort of external threat

00:06:59.200 --> 00:07:01.000 align:middle line:90%
or eternal damnation.

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:03.070 align:middle line:84%
Here it's the salvation
from time itself.

00:07:03.070 --> 00:07:05.770 align:middle line:84%
Once again, this is the kind of
ever present theme in science

00:07:05.770 --> 00:07:08.830 align:middle line:84%
fiction, is that we're doomed
to repeat these loops--

00:07:08.830 --> 00:07:10.930 align:middle line:84%
eternal return that
Nietzsche talked about.

00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:14.860 align:middle line:84%
You know, John Connor is
basically the human savior.

00:07:14.860 --> 00:07:18.070 align:middle line:84%
He's got to free us from
this pre-determined nuclear

00:07:18.070 --> 00:07:19.300 align:middle line:90%
apocalypse.

00:07:19.300 --> 00:07:21.300 align:middle line:84%
And so that's what we're
looking at in this clip

00:07:21.300 --> 00:07:23.950 align:middle line:84%
is that Skynet has
basically become self-aware.

00:07:23.950 --> 00:07:26.650 align:middle line:84%
This is the giant AI program
that-- that basically

00:07:26.650 --> 00:07:29.210 align:middle line:84%
runs the planet in
the dystopian future.

00:07:29.210 --> 00:07:32.979 align:middle line:84%
So how can we get free from
this pre-determined time loop?

00:07:32.979 --> 00:07:35.020 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, they never really
answered the question,

00:07:35.020 --> 00:07:36.686 align:middle line:84%
because I don't think
you can answer it.

00:07:36.686 --> 00:07:40.210 align:middle line:84%
Because it's such a mind
screw, this whole the God--

00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:41.920 align:middle line:84%
the grandfather
complex, I think it's

00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:44.080 align:middle line:84%
called, where you go back
and kill your grandfather

00:07:44.080 --> 00:07:46.210 align:middle line:84%
and, you know, stop
him from being born.

00:07:46.210 --> 00:07:47.980 align:middle line:84%
So how did you do
it to begin with?

00:07:47.980 --> 00:07:51.130 align:middle line:84%
And Cameron and all
the other filmmakers

00:07:51.130 --> 00:07:53.480 align:middle line:84%
really want to play with
this, and it is a great idea.

00:07:53.480 --> 00:07:54.280 align:middle line:90%
Let's face it.

00:07:54.280 --> 00:07:56.140 align:middle line:84%
It's a great science
fiction idea,

00:07:56.140 --> 00:07:57.970 align:middle line:84%
and they play it
to the hilt here.

00:07:57.970 --> 00:08:01.420 align:middle line:84%
But what I like
about this clip is

00:08:01.420 --> 00:08:04.720 align:middle line:84%
that we're kind
of showing that we

00:08:04.720 --> 00:08:07.420 align:middle line:84%
are going to have
to rebel physically

00:08:07.420 --> 00:08:09.970 align:middle line:84%
against this AI
that's coming at us.

00:08:09.970 --> 00:08:11.620 align:middle line:90%
And I actually have--

00:08:11.620 --> 00:08:15.600 align:middle line:84%
very familiar with technocracy
and the coming technocracy.

00:08:15.600 --> 00:08:18.135 align:middle line:84%
And I-- these guys
are out of control.

00:08:18.135 --> 00:08:20.260 align:middle line:84%
And they're building stuff,
and no one is watching.

00:08:20.260 --> 00:08:22.750 align:middle line:84%
And I'm really kind of
worried about what I'm seeing.

00:08:22.750 --> 00:08:23.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:08:23.550 --> 00:08:24.670 align:middle line:90%
>> And I talk to people--

00:08:24.670 --> 00:08:27.970 align:middle line:84%
you know, futurists
and things-- and they

00:08:27.970 --> 00:08:32.200 align:middle line:84%
don't really care about what
effects these inventions are

00:08:32.200 --> 00:08:34.120 align:middle line:90%
going to have on all of us.

00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:36.909 align:middle line:84%
And we're really heading
towards a kind of a surveillance

00:08:36.909 --> 00:08:40.369 align:middle line:84%
nightmare, in which our own TVs
and computers are watching us.

00:08:40.369 --> 00:08:41.169 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:08:41.169 --> 00:08:44.020 align:middle line:84%
>> And when they do
build the terminator,

00:08:44.020 --> 00:08:46.420 align:middle line:84%
which they are
working on, trust me.

00:08:46.420 --> 00:08:49.210 align:middle line:84%
In these agencies within the
Black Ops and the military,

